text: The King and Queen , accompanied by the Princess Mary , and attended by the Right Hon . Edward Shortt , M.P. ( Secretary of State for the Home Department , Minister in Attend ance ) and the Ladies and Gentlemen in Waiting , disembarked from the Royal Yacht and landed at Ramsey , and proceeded by motor - car to Douglas , accompanied by the Lieutenant - Governor and Mrs. Fry , the Governor's Secretary , and the Chief Constable . On their Majesties ' arrival at Douglas the following had the honour of being presented to the King and Queen by the Lieutenant Governor - The Bishop of Sodor and Man , the Members of the Legislative Council , the Speaker of the House of Keys , and the Chair man of the Harbour Commissioners .

text: The Band of the Grenadier Guards played a selection of music during the Investiture , under the direction of Captain A. Williams . The Earl of Stradbroke was received in audience by The King and kissed hands upon his appointment as Governor of Victoria , when His Majesty conferred upon him the honour of Knighthood and invested him with the Insignia of a Knight Commander of the Most Distinguished Order of St. Michael and St. George , and of a Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire ( Military Division ) . The King also invested the Countess of Strad broke with the Insignia of an Officer of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire ( Civil Division ) . The Earl and Countess of Stradbroke sub sequently had the honour of being invited to Luncheon with Their Majesties . The Right Hon . D. Lloyd George , M.P. ( Prime Minister and First Lord of the Treasury ) had an audience of The King , and Vice - Admiral Sir Michael Culme - Seymour , Bt . ( upon relin quishing his appointment as Rear - Admiral Second - in - Command of the Mediterranean Fleet ) had the honour of being received by His Majesty . The Duke of York , attended by Captain the Hon . James Stuart , visited the Motor Exhibi tion at Olympia this morning . The Prince Henry arrived at the Palace from MARLBOROUGH HOUSE , Nov. 10 . Queen Alexandra received at Marlborough House the Members of the Military and Civil Nursing Services who have been awarded the Royal Red Cross , subsequent to the Investiture at Buckingham Palace this morning . Miss A. B. Smith ( Matron - in - Chief , Queen Alexandra's Imperial Military Nursing Service ) was also received by Her Majesty .

text: The Band of the Grenadier Guards played a selection of music during the Investiture , under the direction of Captain A. Williams . The Earl of Stradbroke was received in audience by The King and kissed hands upon his appointment as Governor of Victoria , when His Majesty conferred upon him the honour of Knighthood and invested him with the Insignia of a Knight Commander of the Most Distinguished Order of St. Michael and St. George , and of a Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire ( Military Division ) . The King also invested the Countess of Strad broke with the Insignia of an Officer of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire ( Civil Division ) . The Earl and Countess of Stradbroke sub sequently had the honour of being invited to Luncheon with Their Majesties . The Right Hon . D. Lloyd George , M.P. ( Prime Minister and First Lord of the Treasury ) had an audience of The King , and Vice - Admiral Sir Michael Culme - Seymour , Bt . ( upon relin quishing his appointment as Rear - Admiral Second - in - Command of the Mediterranean Fleet ) had the honour of being received by His Majesty . The Duke of York , attended by Captain the Hon . James Stuart , visited the Motor Exhibi tion at Olympia this morning . The Prince Henry arrived at the Palace from MARLBOROUGH HOUSE , Nov. 10 . Queen Alexandra received at Marlborough House the Members of the Military and Civil Nursing Services who have been awarded the Royal Red Cross , subsequent to the Investiture at Buckingham Palace this morning . Miss A. B. Smith ( Matron - in - Chief , Queen Alexandra's Imperial Military Nursing Service ) was also received by Her Majesty .

The Earl of Stradbroke was received in audience by The King and kissed hands upon his appointment as Governor of Victoria , when His Majesty conferred upon him the honour of Knighthood and invested him with the Insignia of a Knight Commander of the Most Distinguished Order of St. Michael and St. George , and of a Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire ( Military Division ) . The King also invested the Countess of Strad broke with the Insignia of an Officer of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire ( Civil Division ) . The Earl and Countess of Stradbroke sub sequently had the honour of being invited to Luncheon with Their Majesties . The Right Hon . D. Lloyd George , M.P. ( Prime Minister and First Lord of the Treasury ) had an audience of The King , and Vice - Admiral Sir Michael Culme - Seymour , Bt . ( upon relin quishing his appointment as Rear - Admiral Second - in - Command of the Mediterranean Fleet ) had the honour of being received by His Majesty . The Duke of York , attended by Captain the Hon . James Stuart , visited the Motor Exhibi tion at Olympia this morning . The Prince Henry arrived at the Palace from MARLBOROUGH HOUSE , Nov. 10 . Queen Alexandra received at Marlborough House the Members of the Military and Civil Nursing Services who have been awarded the Royal Red Cross , subsequent to the Investiture at Buckingham Palace this morning . Miss A. B. Smith ( Matron - in - Chief , Queen Alexandra's Imperial Military Nursing Service ) was also received by Her Majesty .

text: and Mr. KENNY : Awarded to his son , the late Lieutenant William Kenny , 4 / 39th Garhwal Rifles , Indian Army . - For most conspicuous bravery and devotion to duty near Kot Kai ( Waziristan ) on January 2. 1920 , when in command of a company holding an advanced covering position , which was repeatedly attacked by the Mahsuds in greatly superior numbers . For over four hours this officer main tahed his position . repulsing three determined attacks , being foremost in the hand - to - hand fighting which took place , and re peatedly engaging the enemy with bomb and bayonet . His gallant leadership undoubtedly saved the situation and kept intact the right flank . on which depended the success of the operations and the safety of the troops in rear . text: Royal Army Service I and lined Corps , Lieutenant Robert KILVERT , York and Lancaster Regi ment , Lieutenant Arthur LISLE . Royal Engineers , Lieutenant George General At the Oratory , Brompton , yesterday morning and Hertfordshire Regiment , Sergeant - Major Joseph LEVY , Cary - Elwes , widow of Captain Windsor Cary - Elwes , List , Regimental Sergeant - Major John HENSHAW , Bedfordshire a Requiem was said , by Father Alan Ross , for Mr. Royal Army Medical Corps , and Captain KNIGHT , Royal and daughter of the late Hon . W. T. Law , who died on July 18 at Nairn . There were present Mr. Cary Elwes and Father Elwes , of Fort Augustus ( sons ) , Mr. for Versailles and will be away till the autumn . The Hon . Mrs. Borras Whiteside has left town Gervase and Lady Winefride Elwes , and their sons , Mr. Guy and Mr. Valentine Elwes . The Hon . Mrs. Porter has arrived in London The funeral took place , at a later hour , at Mortlake . from Rocksavage , Dublin .

To - day being the Anniversary of the death of Her late Majesty Queen Victoria , the Royal Mausoleum at Frogmore was open , by The King's Commands , between the hours of 12 and 3 o'clock , for the servants and their families to visit it , when permission to pass through was extended to some of the residents of Windsor and the neighbourhood .
